title: Grateful Dead Live at Music Hall on 1972-09-15
lineage: Dat (Sony R500) -> Sound Devices 744T -> Adobe Audition CC 2015 ->Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, Greatest Story Ever Told, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Black Throated Wind, Tennessee Jed, El Paso, Loser, Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones

Set 2

He's Gone-> Me & My Uncle, Bird Song, Mexicali Blues, Ramble On Rose, Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Can't go wrong with '72.... ....and this stellar showing by the Boyz is a prime example of that notion. Outstanding, eclectic setlist....and spot on execution. Stellar sound. This recording is 43 years old? Could've fooled me....

Thank you There are only a few shows that are as much of a pleasure as this gem. You could not ask for anything more considering this hasn't circulated. This tour is where Grateful Dead were fantastic.

Thanks! Great job as always, Charlie.  I love fall of the '72, and these are some heavy hitters.  Really cool china -> rider, playin, he's gone, bird song, and of the course truckin -> other one > sugar magnolia.  Cant wait to hear the next Charlie Miller remaster!
Wicked Good! Thanks, Cha-lee and co. for a wicked awesome job bringing this monstah of a show to all of us grateful deadheads!

Why do I attach meaning? To my birthday show? Just like any other day. Anyway, I am glad to see it here and this is the day I came into this crazy world. Thanks to the people who made it possible. No not my Mom and Dad (love you Mom and Dad), but to the people who made this recording possible. And also to Mom and Dad!

Solid show Great sounding Fall 72 show, thank you Mr. Charlie.  As noted in another review, the last two songs are from an aud source that is not on par with the rest of the show, lots of tape warble.
